## CORE FEATURES & MODULES

### 1. CRM & LEADS MANAGEMENT
**Purpose:** Complete customer relationship management system

**Features:**
- Lead capture from multiple sources (website forms, Zillow, Realtor.com, Facebook, inbound SMS, inbound calls, blog, webinar)
- Customizable pipeline stages (New, Contacted, Qualified, Proposal, Won, Lost)
- Lead scoring with automated tier assignment (Cold, Warm, Hot, Qualified)
- Custom fields and tags for segmentation
- Activity timeline and interaction history
- Import/export leads (CSV, Excel, leads, contacts)
- Bulk actions and mass updates
- Lead assignment and routing rules
- Duplicate detection and merging
- Search and advanced filtering

**API Endpoints:**
- GET /api/leads - List all leads with pagination and filters
- POST /api/leads - Create new lead
- GET /api/leads/{lead_id} - Get specific lead
- PUT /api/leads/{lead_id} - Update lead
- DELETE /api/leads/{lead_id} - Delete lead
- POST /api/leads/{lead_id}/tags - Add tags to lead
- DELETE /api/leads/{lead_id}/tags - Remove tags from lead
- POST /api/leads/import - Import leads from CSV
- GET /api/leads/export - Export leads to CSV

**Database Collections:**
- leads: Main lead records with all contact info and metadata
- lead_activities: Timeline of interactions (calls, emails, meetings, forms)
- lead_notes: User-added notes and comments

### 2. INDUSTRY-SPECIFIC TEMPLATES & TAGS
**Purpose:** Pre-configured tags, workflows, and AI chatbots per industry

**Industries Covered:**
- Healthcare: doctors, dentists, chiropractors, therapists, veterinarians
- Home Services: plumbers, electricians, HVAC, contractors, landscapers
- Professional Services: lawyers, accountants, real estate, insurance, consultants
- Emergency Services: police, fire, EMS, security
- Automotive: dealerships, repair shops, detailing, towing

**Features per Industry:**
- 10 pre-configured tags with semantic colors
- 5 workflow templates with triggers and actions
- AI chatbot templates with intents, keywords, and responses, knowledge, memory
- Industry-specific automation rules
- Custom field recommendations
- Sample pipeline stages

**Example - Doctors:**
- Tags: New Patient, Follow-up, Insurance Pending, Prescription Refill, Lab Results, Specialist Referral, Annual Checkup, Urgent Care, Telemedicine, Payment Plan
- Workflows: Patient Onboarding, Prescription Refill Automation, Lab Results Follow-up
- Chatbot Intents: schedule_appointment, insurance_question, prescription_refill

**Example - Plumbers:**
- Tags: Emergency Call, Scheduled Maintenance, Quote Requested, Job in Progress, Job Complete, Follow-up Needed, Leak Repair, Drain Cleaning, Water Heater, Warranty Work
- Workflows: Emergency Dispatch, Quote Follow-up Sequence
- Chatbot Intents: emergency_service, quote_request, schedule_maintenance

**API Endpoints:**
- GET /api/industry-templates/industries - Get all industry categories
- GET /api/industry-templates/industries/{industry}/tags - Get tags for industry
- GET /api/industry-templates/user/settings - Get user's industry selection
- PUT /api/industry-templates/user/settings - Save industry and apply tags
- POST /api/industry-templates/user/custom-tags - Create custom tag
- PUT /api/industry-templates/user/custom-tags/{tag_id} - Edit tag
- DELETE /api/industry-templates/user/custom-tags/{tag_id} - Delete tag
- GET /api/industry-templates/workflow-templates/{industry} - Get workflow templates
- GET /api/industry-templates/chatbot-templates/{industry} - Get AI chatbot config

### 3. AI-POWERED WORKFLOWS & AUTOMATION
**Purpose:** Automate repetitive tasks and workflows with AI

**Key Workflows:**

**A. AI Webinar Assistant**
- Monitors all webinar/call conversations
- Detects trigger keywords (e.g., "prescription", "invoice", "insurance claim")
- Auto-fills forms and documents during conversation
- Sends data to external systems (pharmacy, insurance, billing)
- Example for Doctors:
  - Detects: "I need a refill for my blood pressure medication"
  - Actions: Verify prescription history → Send to Walgreens API → SMS patient → Update chart
  - Time saved: 30 minutes per prescription

**B. Emergency Dispatch Workflow**
- AI detects emergency trigger keywords (burst pipe, no heat, chest pain, fire)
- Automatically dispatches nearest technician/responder
- Sends GPS tracking link to customer
- Real-time ETA updates via SMS
- Notifies emergency contacts if needed

**C. Lead Nurture Sequences**
- Automated follow-up emails/SMS based on lead behavior
- Drip campaigns with conditional logic
- A/B testing for messaging optimization
- Engagement tracking and scoring
- Automatic escalation for hot leads

**D. Appointment Reminder System**
- Multi-channel reminders (email, SMS, voice call)
- Configurable intervals (7 days, 3 days, 1 day, 2 hours before)
- Two-way confirmation and rescheduling
- No-show reduction by 60%
- Calendar sync (Google, Outlook, Apple)

**E. Review Generation Automation**
- Triggers after successful job completion
- Timing optimization (24-48 hours post-service)
- Multi-platform posting (Google, Facebook, Trustpilot)
- Negative review alerts for damage control
- Incentive management for review rewards

**API Endpoints:**
- GET /api/automations - List all automations
- POST /api/automations - Create automation
- PUT /api/automations/{id} - Update automation
- DELETE /api/automations/{id} - Delete automation
- POST /api/automations/{id}/trigger - Manual trigger execution
- GET /api/automations/{id}/history - Execution history and logs

### 4. EMERGENCY SERVICES PLATFORM (EPS)
**Purpose:** Integrate emergency response with 911, GPS tracking, and instant dispatch

**Key Features:**
- **Emergency Activation:** One-button SOS or voice trigger keywords with automatic 911 dial
- **GPS Tracking:** Real-time location sharing with emergency contacts
- **Reverse Child Location:** Track family members' locations
- **GoBrunch Emergency Video Rooms:** Instant video connection with responders
- **Emergency Contact Network:** Auto-notify up to 10 emergency contacts
- **Medical Profile:** Store allergies, medications, conditions, blood type
- **Emergency Session Recording:** All communications logged for review
- **Integration with 911:** Direct API connection to emergency dispatch centers

**Emergency Workflows:**
1. User activates emergency (button press or voice command)
2. System captures GPS coordinates and user profile, activate user mobile video, audio, gps, and other data collected.
3. Automatic 911 dial with location data transmission
4. SMS blast to emergency contacts with tracking link
5. GoBrunch video room created and shared
6. All communications recorded to incident report
7. Follow-up health monitoring and check-ins

**API Endpoints:**
- POST /api/emergency/activate - Activate emergency with type and location
- GET /api/emergency/profile - Get user's emergency profile
- PUT /api/emergency/profile - Update emergency profile and contacts
- POST /api/emergency/contacts - Add emergency contact
- GET /api/emergency/sessions - List past emergency sessions
- GET /api/emergency/sessions/{session_id} - Get emergency session details

### 5. HEALTH & MEDICAL TRACKING
**Purpose:** Proactive health monitoring for doctors and patients

**Features:**
- **Vital Signs Monitoring:** Blood pressure, heart rate, glucose, temperature, oxygen
- **Threshold Alerts:** Automatic notifications when vitals exceed set limits
- **Doctor Dashboard:** Real-time view of all patients' health status
- **Patient Portal:** Self-service vital logging and history
- **Medication Reminders:** Automated SMS/email for prescription schedules
- **Lab Results Integration:** Auto-import from labs, notify patient and doctor
- **Appointment Correlation:** Link vitals to visit dates for trend analysis
- **Family Health Tracking:** Monitor elderly parents or children remotely
- **Emergency Escalation:** Auto-trigger EPS if critical vitals detected

**Health Monitoring Workflow:**
1. Patient logs vitals via mobile app or synced devices
2. System compares to doctor-set thresholds
3. If variance >10% (or custom %), alert sent to both
4. Doctor receives summary with recent history
5. System suggests appointment booking
6. Prescription refills auto-requested if needed
7. Reduces ER visits by catching issues early

**API Endpoints:**
- POST /api/health/vitals - Log vital signs
- GET /api/health/vitals - Get vital history with date range
- PUT /api/health/thresholds - Set alert thresholds
- GET /api/health/alerts - Get triggered alerts
- GET /api/health/analytics - Health trends and insights

### 6. INTELLIGENT REPORTS WITH AI intelligence
**Purpose:** Automatically generate professional reports from conversations and data and listen for keyword custom values

**Report Types:**

**A. Emergency Incident Reports**
- Auto-generated from emergency sessions
- Police/Fire/Medical format compliance
- Evidence transcription (photos, videos, audio, location, time, people involved, responders involved)
- Witness statements compilation
- Timeline reconstruction
- Officer/responder signature fields
- Auto-sync to Google Sheets for agency records

**B. Health & Medical Reports**
- Patient visit summaries for doctors
- Discharge instructions for patients
- Insurance claim documentation
- Lab results interpretation
- Treatment plan documents
- Prescription history reports
- HIPAA-compliant formatting

**C. Webinar Intelligence Reports**
- Action items extracted from meeting
- Key decisions and follow-ups
- Trigger word tracking (invoice, offer, deadline)
- Custom value extraction (prices, dates, names)
- Attendee engagement metrics
- Recording transcription and summary

**D. Business Performance Reports**
- Lead conversion funnels
- Revenue by source/campaign
- Team performance metrics
- Customer satisfaction trends
- ROI calculations per channel

**Report Generation Process:**
1. AI transcribes conversation/data
2. Identifies key entities (people, places, actions, numbers)
3. Applies professional writing style per report type
4. Formats in industry-standard template
5. Auto-fills all available fields
6. Sends to designated recipients
7. Syncs to Google Sheets for backup
8. Stores in user's report library

**API Endpoints:**
- POST /api/reports/emergency/generate - Generate emergency report
- POST /api/reports/health/generate - Generate health report
- POST /api/reports/webinar/generate - Generate webinar report
- GET /api/reports/list - List all generated reports
- GET /api/reports/{report_id} - Get specific report
- POST /api/reports/{report_id}/share - Share report via email

