## KEY DIFFERENTIATORS VS COMPETITORS

### vs GoHighLevel
- **Industry-Specific:** GHL is generic, GoogleHubs has 20+ industry templates
- **Emergency Services:** GHL has no EPS, GoogleHubs has 911 integration
- **Health Monitoring:** GHL has no vital tracking, GoogleHubs monitors patient health proactively
- **AI Webinar Assistant:** GHL has basic webinars, GoogleHubs has AI that auto-fills invoices/prescriptions from conversations
- **Smart Home:** GHL has no IoT control, GoogleHubs controls 50+ device types
- **Price:** GHL $297-497/month, GoogleHubs $199-499/month with more features

### vs Salesforce
- **Ease of Use:** Salesforce requires IT staff, GoogleHubs is plug-and-play
- **Price:** Salesforce $1,250-3,000/month, GoogleHubs $299-499/month
- **All-in-One:** Salesforce requires 10+ add-ons, GoogleHubs includes everything
- **Healthcare Compliance:** Salesforce Health Cloud is expensive, GoogleHubs HIPAA included
- **Implementation:** Salesforce takes 6-12 months, GoogleHubs ready in 1 day

### vs ServiceTitan
- **Target Market:** ServiceTitan only for home services, GoogleHubs for 20+ industries
- **Price:** ServiceTitan $300-500/month + fees, GoogleHubs $199-349/month
- **AI Features:** ServiceTitan has basic automation, GoogleHubs has advanced AI
- **Emergency Integration:** ServiceTitan has dispatch, GoogleHubs has full EPS
- **Content Marketing:** ServiceTitan has none, GoogleHubs has full content studio

### vs Kareo / athenahealth
- **Beyond EHR:** Kareo is just medical billing, GoogleHubs is full practice management
- **Marketing:** Medical EMRs have no marketing tools, GoogleHubs has full CRM
- **Smart Home:** Medical software doesn't integrate home health devices, GoogleHubs does
- **Emergency Services:** EMRs don't have EPS, GoogleHubs integrates 911 for urgent care
- **Price:** athenahealth $140-500/provider, GoogleHubs $299 for whole practice

