## USER FLOWS & JOURNEYS

### New User Onboarding Flow
1. Sign up page → Select industry (optional)
2. Email verification (magic link or password)
3. Welcome screen with quick setup wizard
4. Step 1: Complete profile (name, business, phone)
5. Step 2: Select subscription plan (7-day trial for all paid plans)
6. Step 3: Industry setup (choose category → auto-apply tags)
7. Step 4: Connect integrations (Google, Stripe, Twilio optional)
8. Step 5: Import existing data (leads, contacts, calendar)
9. Onboarding checklist appears in dashboard:
   - ✓ Create first lead
   - ✓ Send first message
   - ✓ Schedule first appointment
   - ✓ Create first automation
   - ✓ Set up emergency profile
   - ✓ Connect smart home devices (optional)
10. Video tutorials and tooltips guide through features
11. Optional: Book 1-on-1 onboarding call with success team

### Lead Capture to Conversion Flow
1. Lead comes in from source (website form, Facebook, referral)
2. System creates lead record with source attribution
3. Auto-assign to sales rep based on routing rules
4. Sales rep notified via email/SMS/push
5. AI chatbot responds immediately to lead
6. Lead scoring algorithm assigns temperature (cold/warm/hot)
7. Automated email sequence starts based on lead score
8. Sales rep calls lead (call logged automatically)
9. Appointment booked during call
10. Calendar event created with automated reminders
11. Lead moved to "Qualified" stage in pipeline
12. Pre-appointment email sent with prep instructions
13. Day-of reminder SMS sent 2 hours before
14. Appointment completed → status updated
15. Post-appointment survey sent automatically
16. Review request sent 24 hours later
17. Lead converted to customer
18. Nurture sequence begins for upsells/referrals

### Emergency Activation Flow (Medical)
1. Patient feels chest pain at home
2. Presses SOS button in app or says "Helix, I have a medical emergency!" or "Helix, I have a police emergency!" or "Helix, I want to report a crime!"
3. System captures GPS location and loads medical profile
4. Automatic 911 dial with location data transmission
5. SMS blast to 3 emergency contacts: "John activated emergency at [address]. GPS: [link]"
6. GoBrunch emergency video room created and shared
7. Doctor receives alert with patient's vital history
8. EMS arrives with full medical context from GoogleHubs
9. All communications recorded to incident report
10. Emergency resolved → system sends follow-up health check
11. Doctor reviews incident report and vital trends
12. Follow-up appointment auto-scheduled
13. Insurance claim documentation auto-generated

### Doctor Prescription Workflow (AI Assistant)
1. Doctor in video call with patient
2. Patient says: "I need a refill for my blood pressure medication"
3. AI Webinar Assistant detects keywords: "refill", "blood pressure", "medication"
4. System looks up patient's prescription history
5. Verifies last refill date and refills remaining
6. AI auto-fills prescription form during conversation
7. Doctor reviews and approves with one click
8. Prescription sent to Walgreens API automatically
9. SMS sent to patient: "Your prescription for Lisinopril is ready at Walgreens on Main St. Pick up anytime. Refills left: 2"
10. Patient chart updated with timestamp and details
11. Insurance claim pre-filled for billing
12. Total time: 30 seconds (vs 30+ minutes manual)
13. Doctor continues call without interruption

### Plumber Emergency Dispatch Flow
1. Customer calls plumbing company at 2 AM
2. AI answers instantly: "Emergency plumbing, I can help!"
3. AI asks: "What's the emergency?" 
4. Customer: "Burst pipe flooding my basement!"
5. AI collects address and takes photo via SMS
6. AI detects emergency keywords: "burst pipe", "flooding"
7. System dispatches nearest on-call technician via SMS
8. Technician receives: "EMERGENCY: Burst pipe at 123 Main St. Customer: John Smith, (555)123-4567"
9. Technician accepts job with one tap
10. Customer receives SMS: "John the plumber is on his way! ETA: 23 minutes. Track him here: [GPS link]"
11. Customer can see technician's photo, rating, and live location
12. Technician arrives, updates status to "On Site"
13. Customer receives SMS: "John has arrived and is assessing the damage."
14. Job completed, technician collects payment via mobile app
15. Customer receives SMS: "Thanks for choosing us! How did we do? [Review link]"
16. Job saved to history with photos, time logs, and invoice
17. Follow-up scheduled for 3 days: "Everything still working well?"

### Real Estate Showing to Closing Flow
1. Lead submits form on agent's website: "I want to see 123 Oak St"
2. Lead created in CRM, tagged as "Buyer - Hot"
3. AI chatbot responds: "Great! I can show you 123 Oak St. When are you available?"
4. Lead replies: "Saturday at 2pm"
5. Appointment auto-created in agent's calendar
6. Confirmation email sent with property details and address
7. GoBrunch virtual tour link sent: "Can't make it in person? Take a virtual tour anytime"
8. Day-of reminder: "Your showing is today at 2pm. Meet Agent Sarah at the property."
9. Agent arrives, uses mobile app to log showing notes and take photos
10. Post-showing, agent texts: "What did you think? Ready to make an offer?"
11. Lead replies: "Yes, let's offer $350k"
12. Agent creates offer document with e-signature request
13. Lead signs offer on phone within 5 minutes
14. Offer submitted, lead moved to "Under Contract" stage
15. Automated milestone tracking: Inspection → Appraisal → Financing → Clear to Close
16. Reminders sent for each deadline
17. Closing completed, lead status changed to "Closed - Won"
18. Thank you gift automatically ordered and shipped
19. Post-closing survey: "How was your experience?"
20. Past client nurture sequence begins: Annual home anniversary, birthday cards, market updates
21. 3 years later: "Thinking of upgrading? Let's chat about your home's value!"

