## TECHNICAL ARCHITECTURE DETAILS

### Authentication Flow
1. User submits email + password to POST /api/auth/login
2. Backend validates credentials with bcrypt
3. JWT token generated with user_id, email, role
4. Token stored in httpOnly cookie (secure, samesite=none)
5. Token also returned in response body for localStorage
6. Frontend stores token and includes in Authorization header
7. Token expires after 7 days
8. Refresh token flow not yet implemented (future enhancement)

### Database Schema (MongoDB)

**users collection:**
```javascript
{
  user_id: "user_abc123",
  email: "doctor@example.com",
  password_hash: "bcrypt_hash_here",
  name: "Dr. Sarah Mitchell",
  role: "user" | "admin" | "super_admin" | "agency",
  created_at: "2025-01-15T10:30:00Z",
  llm_connections: {
    gemini: { active: true, is_default: true },
    openai: { active: false }
  },
  subscription: {
    plan_id: "default_professional",
    status: "active",
    billing_cycle: "monthly"
  }
}
```

**leads collection:**
```javascript
{
  lead_id: "lead_xyz789",
  user_id: "user_abc123",
  name: "John Smith",
  email: "john@example.com",
  phone: "+15551234567",
  company: "Smith & Co",
  status: "qualified",
  source: "website_form",
  value: 5000,
  tags: ["hot-lead", "enterprise"],
  custom_fields: {},
  created_at: "2025-01-20T14:22:00Z",
  updated_at: "2025-01-21T09:15:00Z"
}
```

**tags collection:**
```javascript
{
  tag_id: "tag_def456",
  user_id: "user_abc123",
  name: "New Patient",
  color: "#10b981",
  category: "status",
  description: "First-time patient",
  is_default: true,
  industry: "doctors",
  created_at: "2025-01-15T10:30:00Z"
}
```

**emergency_sessions collection:**
```javascript
{
  session_id: "emerg_ghi789",
  user_id: "user_abc123",
  emergency_type: "medical",
  priority: "critical",
  status: "active",
  location: {
    latitude: 40.7128,
    longitude: -74.0060,
    address: "123 Main St, New York, NY 10001"
  },
  contacts_notified: ["contact1@example.com", "contact2@example.com"],
  gobrunch_room_url: "https://gobrunch.com/room/emerg123",
  created_at: "2025-01-22T03:45:00Z"
}
```

### API Response Format
```javascript
// Success response
{
  "success": true,
  "data": { /* response data */ },
  "message": "Operation completed successfully"
}

// Error response
{
  "success": false,
  "error": "Error message here",
  "detail": "Detailed error information",
  "status_code": 400
}
```

### WebSocket Protocol
- Connection: ws://backend:8001/ws/{user_id}
- Authentication: Token sent in initial message
- Message format: JSON with type and payload
- Types: notification, lead_update, emergency_alert, task_reminder
- Heartbeat: Ping every 30 seconds to keep connection alive

### File Upload Strategy
- Max file size: 10MB per file
- Allowed types: images (jpg, png, webp), documents (pdf, docx), videos (mp4, mov)
- Storage: Local filesystem in /app/backend/uploads
- Path structure: /uploads/{user_id}/{file_type}/{filename}
- Future: Migrate to AWS S3 or Google Cloud Storage

### Caching Strategy
- No Redis/caching layer currently implemented
- Future: Add Redis for session management and frequently accessed data
- Cache TTL: 5-60 minutes depending on data type
- Cache invalidation: On CRUD operations

