## HOW TO REPLICATE THIS PLATFORM

### Step 1: Set Up Development Environment
```bash
# Backend
cd /app/backend
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Frontend
cd /app/frontend
yarn install

# MongoDB
# Install MongoDB Community Edition or use MongoDB Atlas
```

### Step 2: Configure Environment Variables
- Copy .env.example to .env in both backend and frontend
- Fill in all API keys (Stripe, Twilio, GoBrunch, etc.)
- Set MONGO_URL to your MongoDB connection string

### Step 3: Run Services
```bash
# Start MongoDB
mongod --dbpath /data/db

# Start Backend (from /app/backend)
uvicorn server:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8001 --reload

# Start Frontend (from /app/frontend)
yarn start
```

### Step 4: Build Core Features in Order
1. Authentication system (JWT, bcrypt, session management)
2. Database models and schemas
3. CRM/Leads CRUD operations
4. Basic UI with React components
5. Calendar and scheduling
6. Communication (email, SMS)
7. Billing integration with Stripe
8. Industry templates system
9. AI integrations (OpenAI, Gemini)
10. Emergency services platform
11. Advanced features (smart home, health, webinars)
12. Sales presentations system
13. Affiliate program
14. Analytics and reporting

### Step 5: Deploy to Production
- Set up Kubernetes cluster
- Configure Docker containers
- Set up Nginx reverse proxy
- Enable SSL/TLS certificates
- Configure domain and DNS
- Set up monitoring and logging
- Enable automated backups

